    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-31T13:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-31T13:45:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/2011: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-31T13:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>372. Referring to my cable of September 11, 4 p.m., and despatch 801 of September
                        20th.<note n="82" xml:id="d492fn82">Latter not printed.</note> I have just
                    received a letter from Benard promising to set aside for the <hi rend="italic"
                        >guardia</hi> $380,000 from the next surplus.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
